channel.title: Papers with Code: Latest (unofficial)
channel.description: As a disclaimer, this is an unofficial feed and has no affiliation with Papers with Code.

item.title: Consistent Estimation of a Class of Distances Between Covariance Matrices
item.description: This family of distances is particularly useful as it takes into consideration the fact that covariance matrices lie in the Riemannian manifold of positive definite matrices, thereby including a variety of commonly used metrics, such as the Euclidean distance, Jeffreys' divergence, and the log-Euclidean distance.

item.title: Handling Long-Term Safety and Uncertainty in Safe Reinforcement Learning
item.description: Safety is one of the key issues preventing the deployment of reinforcement learning techniques in real-world robots.

item.title: multiPI-TransBTS: A Multi-Path Learning Framework for Brain Tumor Image Segmentation Based on Multi-Physical Information
item.description: Brain Tumor Segmentation (BraTS) plays a critical role in clinical diagnosis, treatment planning, and monitoring the progression of brain tumors.

item.title: Multi-Grid Graph Neural Networks with Self-Attention for Computational Mechanics
item.description: This paper introduces a novel model merging Self-Attention with Message Passing in GNNs, achieving a 15\% reduction in RMSE on the well known flow past a cylinder benchmark.

item.title: Gradient-Driven 3D Segmentation and Affordance Transfer in Gaussian Splatting Using 2D Masks
item.description: As a byproduct, we discovered that inference-time gradients can also be used to prune Gaussians, resulting in up to 21% compression.

item.title: Revealing the Challenge of Detecting Character Knowledge Errors in LLM Role-Playing
item.description: Large language model (LLM) role-playing has gained widespread attention, where the authentic character knowledge is crucial for constructing realistic LLM role-playing agents.

item.title: PhysMamba: Efficient Remote Physiological Measurement with SlowFast Temporal Difference Mamba
item.description: Facial-video based Remote photoplethysmography (rPPG) aims at measuring physiological signals and monitoring heart activity without any contact, showing significant potential in various applications.

item.title: A Controlled Study on Long Context Extension and Generalization in LLMs
item.description: Broad textual understanding and in-context learning require language models that utilize full document contexts.

item.title: All-in-one foundational models learning across quantum chemical levels
item.description: Here we introduce the all-in-one (AIO) ANI model architecture based on multimodal learning which can learn an arbitrary number of QC levels.

item.title: Vista3D: Unravel the 3D Darkside of a Single Image
item.description: We embark on the age-old quest: unveiling the hidden dimensions of objects from mere glimpses of their visible parts.

item.title: FedLF: Adaptive Logit Adjustment and Feature Optimization in Federated Long-Tailed Learning
item.description: Extensive experiments on benchmark datasets CIFAR-10-LT and CIFAR-100-LT demonstrate that our approach effectively mitigates the problem of model performance degradation due to data heterogeneity and long-tailed distribution.

item.title: MAgICoRe: Multi-Agent, Iterative, Coarse-to-Fine Refinement for Reasoning
item.description: Moreover, to ensure effective refinement, we employ a multi-agent loop with three agents: Solver, Reviewer (which generates targeted feedback based on step-wise RM scores), and the Refiner (which incorporates feedback).

item.title: Symmetry-Based Structured Matrices for Efficient Approximately Equivariant Networks
item.description: In this work, we propose a general framework -- based on a novel construction of symmetry-based structured matrices -- to build approximately equivariant NNs with significantly reduced parameter counts.

item.title: Synthesizing Evolving Symbolic Representations for Autonomous Systems
item.description: Deep Reinforcement Learning(DRL) is an effective tool for agents to learn policies in low-level state spaces to solve highly complex tasks.

item.title: DAF-Net: A Dual-Branch Feature Decomposition Fusion Network with Domain Adaptive for Infrared and Visible Image Fusion
item.description: Infrared and visible image fusion aims to combine complementary information from both modalities to provide a more comprehensive scene understanding.

item.title: MEOW: MEMOry Supervised LLM Unlearning Via Inverted Facts
item.description: LLM Unlearning, a post-hoc approach to remove this information from trained LLMs, offers a promising solution to mitigate these risks.

item.title: Unraveling the Hessian: A Key to Smooth Convergence in Loss Function Landscapes
item.description: The loss landscape of neural networks is a critical aspect of their training, and understanding its properties is essential for improving their performance.

item.title: Fitting Multilevel Factor Models
item.description: We show that the inverse of an invertible PSD MLR matrix is also an MLR matrix with the same sparsity in factors, and we use the recursive Sherman-Morrison-Woodbury matrix identity to obtain the factors of the inverse.

item.title: TART: An Open-Source Tool-Augmented Framework for Explainable Table-based Reasoning
item.description: Current Large Language Models (LLMs) exhibit limited ability to understand table structures and to apply precise numerical reasoning, which is crucial for tasks such as table question answering (TQA) and table-based fact verification (TFV).

item.title: ChefFusion: Multimodal Foundation Model Integrating Recipe and Food Image Generation
item.description: Significant work has been conducted in the domain of food computing, yet these studies typically focus on single tasks such as t2t (instruction generation from food titles and ingredients), i2t (recipe generation from food images), or t2i (food image generation from recipes).

item.title: Qwen2-VL: Enhancing Vision-Language Model's Perception of the World at Any Resolution
item.description: We present the Qwen2-VL Series, an advanced upgrade of the previous Qwen-VL models that redefines the conventional predetermined-resolution approach in visual processing.

item.title: Measuring Human and AI Values based on Generative Psychometrics with Large Language Models
item.description: This work introduces Generative Psychometrics for Values (GPV), an LLM-based, data-driven value measurement paradigm, theoretically grounded in text-revealed selective perceptions.

item.title: Computational Imaging for Long-Term Prediction of Solar Irradiance
item.description: The occlusion of the sun by clouds is one of the primary sources of uncertainties in solar power generation, and is a factor that affects the wide-spread use of solar power as a primary energy source.

item.title: Lite-FBCN: Lightweight Fast Bilinear Convolutional Network for Brain Disease Classification from MRI Image
item.description: Achieving high accuracy with computational efficiency in brain disease classification from Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) scans is challenging, particularly when both coarse and fine-grained distinctions are crucial.

item.title: Mamba Fusion: Learning Actions Through Questioning
item.description: Video Language Models (VLMs) are crucial for generalizing across diverse tasks and using language cues to enhance learning.

item.title: OmniGen: Unified Image Generation
item.description: In this work, we introduce OmniGen, a new diffusion model for unified image generation.

item.title: Gradient-free Post-hoc Explainability Using Distillation Aided Learnable Approach
item.description: In this paper, we propose a framework, named distillation aided explainability (DAX), that attempts to generate a saliency-based explanation in a model agnostic gradient free application.

item.title: STCMOT: Spatio-Temporal Cohesion Learning for UAV-Based Multiple Object Tracking
item.description: Multiple object tracking (MOT) in Unmanned Aerial Vehicle (UAV) videos is important for diverse applications in computer vision.

item.title: Sample Complexity Bounds for Linear System Identification from a Finite Set
item.description: This paper considers a finite sample perspective on the problem of identifying an LTI system from a finite set of possible systems using trajectory data.

item.title: Propulsion: Steering LLM with Tiny Fine-Tuning
item.description: The rapid advancements in Large Language Models (LLMs) have revolutionized natural language processing (NLP) and related fields.

item.title: Temporal As a Plugin: Unsupervised Video Denoising with Pre-Trained Image Denoisers
item.description: Recent advancements in deep learning have shown impressive results in image and video denoising, leveraging extensive pairs of noisy and noise-free data for supervision.

item.title: SkinMamba: A Precision Skin Lesion Segmentation Architecture with Cross-Scale Global State Modeling and Frequency Boundary Guidance
item.description: Skin lesion segmentation is a crucial method for identifying early skin cancer.

item.title: BAD: Bidirectional Auto-regressive Diffusion for Text-to-Motion Generation
item.description: Autoregressive models excel in modeling sequential dependencies by enforcing causal constraints, yet they struggle to capture complex bidirectional patterns due to their unidirectional nature.

item.title: Promptriever: Instruction-Trained Retrievers Can Be Prompted Like Language Models
item.description: Instruction-tuned language models (LM) are able to respond to imperative commands, providing a more natural user interface compared to their base counterparts.

item.title: SynthSOD: Developing an Heterogeneous Dataset for Orchestra Music Source Separation
item.description: Recent advancements in music source separation have significantly progressed, particularly in isolating vocals, drums, and bass elements from mixed tracks.

item.title: Time-Series Forecasting, Knowledge Distillation, and Refinement within a Multimodal PDE Foundation Model
item.description: We propose a new token library based on SymPy to encode differential equations as an additional modality for time-series models.

item.title: Fast Analysis of the OpenAI O1-Preview Model in Solving Random K-SAT Problem: Does the LLM Solve the Problem Itself or Call an External SAT Solver?
item.description: In this manuscript I present an analysis on the performance of OpenAI O1-preview model in solving random K-SAT instances for K$\in {2, 3, 4}$ as a function of $\alpha=M/N$ where $M$ is the number of clauses and $N$ is the number of variables of the satisfiable problem.

item.title: Annealed Winner-Takes-All for Motion Forecasting
item.description: Additionally, to compensate for limited performance, some approaches rely on training with a large set of hypotheses, requiring a post-selection step during inference to significantly reduce the number of predictions.

item.title: LC-Protonets: Multi-label Few-shot learning for world music audio tagging
item.description: We introduce Label-Combination Prototypical Networks (LC-Protonets) to address the problem of multi-label few-shot classification, where a model must generalize to new classes based on only a few available examples.

item.title: Measuring and Enhancing Trustworthiness of LLMs in RAG through Grounded Attributions and Learning to Refuse
item.description: While many studies focus on evaluating the quality of end-to-end RAG systems, there is a lack of research on understanding the appropriateness of an LLM for the RAG task.

item.title: Neural Fields for Adaptive Photoacoustic Computed Tomography
item.description: Photoacoustic computed tomography (PACT) is a non-invasive imaging modality with wide medical applications.

item.title: A Physics Informed Neural Network (PINN) Methodology for Coupled Moving Boundary PDEs
item.description: Physics-Informed Neural Network (PINN) is a novel multi-task learning framework useful for solving physical problems modeled using differential equations (DEs) by integrating the knowledge of physics and known constraints into the components of deep learning.

item.title: The Art of Storytelling: Multi-Agent Generative AI for Dynamic Multimodal Narratives
item.description: This paper introduces the concept of an education tool that utilizes Generative Artificial Intelligence (GenAI) to enhance storytelling for children.

item.title: VALO: A Versatile Anytime Framework for LiDAR-based Object Detection Deep Neural Networks
item.description: This work addresses the challenge of adapting dynamic deadline requirements for LiDAR object detection deep neural networks (DNNs).

item.title: Reasoning Graph Enhanced Exemplars Retrieval for In-Context Learning
item.description: Large language models(LLMs) have exhibited remarkable few-shot learning capabilities and unified the paradigm of NLP tasks through the in-context learning(ICL) technique.

item.title: Advances in APPFL: A Comprehensive and Extensible Federated Learning Framework
item.description: Federated learning (FL) is a distributed machine learning paradigm enabling collaborative model training while preserving data privacy.

item.title: CORE-Bench: Fostering the Credibility of Published Research Through a Computational Reproducibility Agent Benchmark
item.description: This paper introduces such a benchmark, designed to measure the accuracy of AI agents in tackling a crucial yet surprisingly challenging aspect of scientific research: computational reproducibility.

item.title: Control-flow Reconstruction Attacks on Business Process Models
item.description: Process models may be automatically generated from event logs that contain as-is data of a business process.

item.title: Chess Rating Estimation from Moves and Clock Times Using a CNN-LSTM
item.description: To overcome this, we explore a method to estimate player ratings directly from game moves and clock times.

item.title: MSDNet: Multi-Scale Decoder for Few-Shot Semantic Segmentation via Transformer-Guided Prototyping
item.description: Our approach introduces the spatial transformer decoder and the contextual mask generation module to improve the relational understanding between support and query images.
